{"formatVersion":"1","manifest":{"sourceId":"chanakya-hi","displayName":"चाणक्य नीति","displayNameEnglish":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","version":"1.0","language":"Hindi","languageCode":"hi","script":"Devanagari","isRTL":false,"transliterationAvailable":false,"edition":"Public Domain & Curated / Hindi Wikiquote","primaryCategory":"Philosophy & Spirituality","subcategory":"Hindi Wisdom","type":"quotes","browseOrder":"sequence","supportsRandom":true,"supportsBrowse":true,"groupingLevels":[],"groupingLabels":[],"sortPriority":51,"contentRating":"general","audienceTags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"itemCount":349,"dataPath":"Data/Collections/ChanakyaNiti_Hindi.json"},"data":[{"id":"chanakya-hi-0001","text":"व्यक्ति अकेले पैदा होता है और अकेले मर जाता है; और वो अपने अच्छे और बुरे कर्मों का फल खुद ही भुगतता है; और वह अकेले ही नर्क या स्वर्ग जाता है।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0002","text":"अगर सांप जहरीला ना भी हो तो उसे खुद को जहरीला दिखाना चाहिए।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0003","text":"शिक्षा सबसे अच्छी मित्र है। एक शिक्षित व्यक्ति हर जगह सम्मान पता है। शिक्षा सौंदर्य और यौवन को परास्त कर देती है।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0004","text":"कोई व्यक्ति अपने कार्यों से महान होता है, अपने जन्म से नहीं।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0005","text":"किसी मूर्ख व्यक्ति के लिए किताबें उतनी ही उपयोगी हैं जितना कि एक अंधे व्यक्ति के लिए आईना।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0006","text":"सर्प, नृप, शेर, डंक मारने वाले ततैया, छोटे बच्चे, दूसरों के कुत्तों, और एक मूर्ख: इन सातों को नींद से नहीं उठाना चाहिए।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0007","text":"इस बात को व्यक्त मत होने दीजिये कि आपने क्या करने के लिए सोचा है, बुद्धिमानी से इसे रहस्य बनाये रखिये और इस काम को करने के लिए दृढ रहिये।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0008","text":"जैसे ही भय आपके करीब आये, उसपर आक्रमण कर उसे नष्ट कर दीजिये।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0009","text":"कोई काम शुरू करने से पहले, स्वयम से तीन प्रश्न कीजिये – मैं ये क्यों कर रहा हूँ, इसके परिणाम क्या हो सकते हैं और क्या मैं सफल होऊंगा। और जब गहरई से सोचने पर इन प्रश्नों के संतोषजनक उत्तर मिल जायें, तभी आगे बढें।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0010","text":"जब तक आपका शरीर स्वस्थ्य और नियंत्रण में है और मृत्यु दूर है, अपनी आत्मा को बचाने कि कोशिश कीजिये; जब मृत्यु सर पर आजायेगी तब आप क्या कर पाएंगे?","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0011","text":"पहले पाच सालों में अपने बच्चे को बड़े प्यार से रखिये। अगले पांच साल उन्हें डांट-डपट के रखिये। जब वह सोलह साल का हो जाये तो उसके साथ एक मित्र की तरह व्यव्हार करिए। आपके व्यस्क बच्चे ही आपके सबसे अच्छे मित्र हैं।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0012","text":"हमें भूत के बारे में पछतावा नहीं करना चाहिए, ना ही भविष्य के बारे में चिंतित होना चाहिए; विवेकवान व्यक्ति हमेशा वर्तमान में जीते हैं।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0013","text":"हर मित्रता के पीछे कोई ना कोई स्वार्थ होता है। ऐसी कोई मित्रता नहीं जिसमे स्वार्थ ना हो। यह कड़वा सच है।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0014","text":"व्यक्ति अकेले ही पैदा होता है और अकेले ही मर जाता है और वो अपने अच्छे और बुरे कर्मो का फल खुद ही भुगतता है। वह अकेले ही नरक या स्वर्ग जाता है।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0015","text":"समय को पहचानना ही मनुष्य के सीखने की सर्वोत्तम कला मानी गई है।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0016","text":"फूलों की सुगंध केवल हवा की दिशा में फैलती है, लेकिन एक इंसान की अच्छाई चारों दिशाओं में फैलती है।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0017","text":"ऋण, शत्रु और रोग को समाप्त कर देना चाहिए।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0018","text":"एक ही देश के दो शत्रु परस्पर मित्र होते हैं।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0019","text":"भगवान मूर्तियों में नहीं है, आपकी अनुभूति आपका इश्वर है, आत्मा आपका मंदिर है।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0020","text":"कुशलता का ज्ञान प्राप्त कर श्रेय की प्राप्ति कर सकता है।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0021","text":"दूसरों की गलतियों से भी सीख लेनी चाहिए, क्योंकि अपने ही ऊपर प्रयोग करने पर तुम्हारी आयु कम पड़ जाएगी।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0022","text":"आपका हमेशा खुश रहना आपके दुश्मनों के लिए सबसे बड़ी सजा है।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0023","text":"लोहे को लोहे से ही काटना चाहिए।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0024","text":"यदि माता दुष्ट है तो उसे भी त्याग देना चाहिए।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0025","text":"सांप को दूध पिलाने से विष ही बढ़ता है, न की अमृत।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0026","text":"भूख के समान कोई दूसरा शत्रु नहीं है।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0027","text":"किसी लक्ष्य की सिद्धि में कभी शत्रु का साथ न करें।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0028","text":"सोने के साथ मिलकर चांदी भी सोने जैसी दिखाई पड़ती है अर्थात सत्संग का प्रभाव मनुष्य पर अवश्य पड़ता है।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0029","text":"जो जिस कार्ये में कुशल हो, उसे उसी कार्ये में लगना चाहिए।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0030","text":"शक्तिशाली शत्रु को कमजोर समझकर ही उस पर आक्रमण करें।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0031","text":"धूर्त व्यक्ति अपने स्वार्थ के लिए दूसरों की सेवा करते हैं।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0032","text":"आग में आग नहीं डालनी चाहिए अर्थात् क्रोधी व्यक्ति को अधिक क्रोध नहीं दिलाना चाहिए।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0033","text":"शासक को स्वयं योग्य बनकर योग्य प्रशासकों की सहायता से शासन करना चाहिए।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0034","text":"यदि खुद कुबेर भी अपनी आय से अधिक खर्च करने लगे तो वह एक दिन निर्धन हो जायेगा।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0035","text":"मूर्खों से अपनी तारीफ सुनने से अच्छा है कि आप किसी बुद्धिमान की डांट सुनें।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0036","text":"भविष्य के अन्धकार में छिपे कार्य के लिए श्रेष्ठ मंत्रणा दीपक के समान प्रकाश देने वाली है।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0037","text":"पडोसी राज्यों से सन्धियां तथा पारस्परिक व्यवहार का आदान-प्रदान और संबंध विच्छेद आदि का निर्वाह मंत्रिमंडल करता है।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0038","text":"कच्चा पात्र कच्चे पात्र से टकराकर टूट जाता है।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0039","text":"व्यक्ति को उट-पटांग अथवा गवार वेशभूषा धारण नहीं करनी चाहिए।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0040","text":"शराबी व्यक्ति का कोई कार्य पूरा नहीं होता है।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0041","text":"बिना उपाय के किए गए कार्य प्रयत्न करने पर भी बचाए नहीं जा सकते, नष्ट हो जाते है।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0042","text":"वेश्याएं निर्धनों के साथ नहीं रहतीं, नागरिक दुर्बलों की संगती में नहीं रहते, और पक्षी उस पेड़ पर घोंसला नहीं बनाते जिसपे फल ना हों।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0043","text":"अपमानित होके जीने से अच्छा मरना है। मृत्यु तो बस एक क्षण का दुःख देती है, लेकिन अपमान हर दिन जीवन में दुःख लाता है।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0044","text":"दुनिया की सबसे बड़ी ताकत पुरुष का विवेक और महिला की सुन्दरता है।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0045","text":"अपने बच्चों को पहले पाँच साल तक खूब प्यार करो, छः साल से पंद्रह साल तक कठोर अनुशासन और संस्कार दो, सोलह साल से उनके साथ मित्रवत व्यवहार करो। आपकी संतति ही आपकी सबसे अच्छी मित्र है।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0046","text":"सुखस्य मूलमर्थः ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0047","text":"अर्थस्य मूलं राज्यम् ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0048","text":"राज्यमूलमिन्द्रियजयः ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0049","text":"इन्द्रियजयस्य मूलं विन्यः ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0050","text":"विन्यस्य मूलं वृद्धसेवा ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0051","text":"विनयेन विद्या ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0052","text":"योगादात्मवत्ता ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0053","text":"आत्मवत्तोत्साहः ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0054","text":"उत्साहात्प्रभावः ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0055","text":"प्रभावात् सिद्धिः ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0056","text":"सिद्धिर्लाभाय ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0057","text":"अविनयस्य मूलमहङ्कारः ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0058","text":"वृद्धसेवया विनयो न नश्यति ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0059","text":"असहायस्य कार्याणि न सिद्ध्यन्ति ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0060","text":"मन्त्री श्रेष्ठः ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0061","text":"मन्त्रिणा मन्त्रो रक्ष्यः ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0062","text":"मन्त्ररक्षणात् कार्यसिद्धिः ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0063","text":"अमात्यैः सह मन्त्रयेत् ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0064","text":"मन्त्रिपरिषदि विचारयेत् ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0065","text":"मन्त्रिभिः कृताः कार्याः ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0066","text":"मन्त्रिसंपत् कार्यसंपत् ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0067","text":"मन्त्रभेदो राज्यनाशः ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0068","text":"मन्त्रो नित्यं रहस्यः ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0069","text":"सर्वकार्येषु मन्त्रिणो नियोगः ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0070","text":"अमात्येषु मन्त्रो न नश्यति ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0071","text":"अमात्यैः सह विचारयेत् ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0072","text":"अमात्येषु कार्यसिद्धिः ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0073","text":"अन्योऽन्यं विचारः श्रेयसे ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0074","text":"अन्यस्य विचारो न ग्राह्यः ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0075","text":"कार्याणां कार्यत्वम् ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0076","text":"अहङ्कारात् क्रोधः ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0077","text":"क्रोधात् दुरत्ययो गुरुः ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0078","text":"मित्रैः प्रेम ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0079","text":"मित्रैः प्रवृत्तिः श्रेयसी ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0080","text":"अमात्यैः प्रवृत्तिः श्रेयसी ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0081","text":"अमात्यैः कार्यसिद्धिः ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0082","text":"राज्यं इन्द्रियजयः ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0083","text":"राज्ञः प्रधानं राज्यम् ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0084","text":"आत्मनः प्रधानमायतनम् ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0085","text":"आत्मनः प्रधानं राज्यम् ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0086","text":"शत्रुः मित्रं भवति ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0087","text":"मित्रं शत्रुः भवति ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0088","text":"तेजः (बलं, शक्ति व उत्कर्ष) हि कार्यसाधकम् ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0089","text":"तेजस्विनामेव जयः ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0090","text":"दुर्बलो राजा न दुर्बलो भवति ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0091","text":"बलवान राजा दुर्बल राजा से सन्धि न करे ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0092","text":"बलवान राजा दुर्बल राजा से युद्ध करे ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0093","text":"बलवान राजा दुर्बल राजा को अपनी सेना के साथ युद्ध करने के लिए समर्थ है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0094","text":"बुद्धिमत् मनुष्य शत्रु को भी मित्र बना लेता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0095","text":"शत्रु के विषय की भली-भाँति जानकारी रखना सुरक्षा देता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0096","text":"दुर्बल राजा बलवान राजा को आश्रय लेता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0097","text":"बलवान राजा दुर्बल राजा का आश्रय लेता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0098","text":"आश्रय राजा के समान रहना चाहिए ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0099","text":"आश्रित राजा का आश्रयदाता के प्रति व्यवहार ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0100","text":"मित्रैः राज्ञः सर्वकार्येषु सहयोगः ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0101","text":"मित्रं राज्ञः सर्वकार्येषु सहयोगः ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0102","text":"विजयकामस्तु परेषु दण्डमादिशेत् ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0103","text":"किसी राजा को परस्पर विरोध में डाल देना चाहिए ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0104","text":"इंद्रियवशवर्ती किसी काम को सिद्ध नहीं कर पाता ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0105","text":"इंद्रियजयी विजय प्राप्त करता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0106","text":"राज्ञः अविचारेण न नश्यति ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0107","text":"राजा अमात्य से मिलकर किसी काम को कर पाता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0108","text":"जब समय अनुकूल हो, तब ही शत्रु पर प्रहार करें।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0109","text":"सीखने वाला कोई वर्ग, उम्र या सीमा नहीं देखता।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0110","text":"वाणी की कठोरता आग की ज्वलन्त से भी अधिक कष्टकर है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0111","text":"राजा अमात्य से संयुक्त होकर सब काम करने में समर्थ होता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0112","text":"शत्रु को वश में करना दंडनीति पर निर्भर करता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0113","text":"दंड से ही संतोष बढ़ता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0114","text":"दंडनीति के अभाव में मतस्यन्याय होता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0115","text":"दंडनीति के कारण ही लोग सरकारी कार्य करने से बचते हैं ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0116","text":"दंडनीति से ही अपनी सुरक्षा होती है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0117","text":"दंड से ही अपनी सुरक्षा होती है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0118","text":"दंड का उपयोग प्रजा और शत्रु दोनों से अपनी रक्षा करता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0119","text":"दंड का उपयोग भले-भाँति सोच-विचार कर करना चाहिए ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0120","text":"किसी को दुर्बल समझकर उसकी उपेक्षा करना उचित नहीं ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0121","text":"आग दुर्बल नहीं होती अर्थात् दुर्बल राजा भी भारी उत्पात मचा सकता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0122","text":"दंड ही व्यवहार का आधार है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0123","text":"अर्थ ही धर्म और काम का मूल है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0124","text":"श्रम थोड़ा भी हो, परंतु यदि कार्य सिद्धि हो जाए तो कार्यसिद्धि हो जाती है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0125","text":"उपयुक्त (सोच-विचार) कार्य की सिद्धि के उपाय ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0126","text":"उपाय (सोच-विचार) के बिना किसी काम को करना कठिन होता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0127","text":"पूर्वपक्षे (साध्य) कार्य सिद्धि प्राप्त करता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0128","text":"उपयुक्त (सोच-विचार) कार्यसिद्धि सहायक ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0129","text":"भाग्य भी पूर्वपक्षे होता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0130","text":"भाग्य के प्रतिकूल होने पर, पूर्वपक्ष में सफलता नहीं मिलती ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0131","text":"भाग्य के प्रतिकूल होने पर, उपयुक्त कार्य असफल होता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0132","text":"मित्रस्य कार्ये हि बुद्धिरतः कार्ये तु बुद्धिरतः ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0133","text":"एक कार्य सिद्ध होने के उपरांत, दूसरे कार्य की सिद्धि के लिए प्रयत्न होना चाहिए ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0134","text":"चित्तैकाग्रता (अधिकरुद्धचिः) व्यक्ति कार्य सिद्ध नहीं कर पाता ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0135","text":"हाथ में आए वस्तु के तिरस्कार से बना हुआ कार्य भी विरुद्ध होता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0136","text":"दोपहर में सोए हुए व्यक्ति का कार्य सिद्ध नहीं होता ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0137","text":"दुःख और कष्ट सहनेवाला व्यक्ति कार्यसिद्धि में सफल होता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0138","text":"समय के साथ चलनेवाला व्यक्ति कार्यसिद्धि में सफल होता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0139","text":"किसी काम को फल मिलने पर ही उसका फल और आनंद प्राप्त होता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0140","text":"कार्यसिद्धि में धैर्य की आवश्यकता ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0141","text":"देश और काल के ज्ञान से कार्य सिद्धि होती है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0142","text":"देव का प्रतिकूल होना कार्यसिद्धि में बाधा डालता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0143","text":"देश-काल का भली-भाँति विचार करनेवाला व्यक्ति लक्ष्मी प्राप्त करता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0144","text":"राजा को काम, दाम आदि सभी उपायों से प्रजा के संबंध में प्रयत्न करना चाहिए ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0145","text":"अविचारणीय व्यक्ति भाग्यशाली होता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0146","text":"प्रत्येक वस्तु की परीक्षा - गुण, अनुमान, उपमान और शब्द से करनी चाहिए ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0147","text":"जो जिस कार्य-विषय में कुशल हो, उसे उसी कार्य में नियुक्त करना चाहिए ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0148","text":"उपयुक्त पुरुष कार्य को भी सहज में ही साथ लेता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0149","text":"उपयुक्त व्यक्ति कार्य को सहज में ही साथ लेता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0150","text":"जो व्यक्ति स्वयं किसी काम को जानता हो, उसे ही नियुक्त करना चाहिए ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0151","text":"शंकाशील व पवित्र आचरण करनेवाले व्यक्ति कार्य में सफल होते हैं ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0152","text":"देव के प्रति आदर और शांति कर्मों का अनुसरण करना चाहिए ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0153","text":"माननीय व्यक्तियों के निराकरण के लिए अपने बुद्धि-कौशल का प्रयोग करना चाहिए ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0154","text":"विपरीत स्थिति में किया गया काम हानिप्रद होता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0155","text":"कार्यसिद्धि के इच्छक व्यक्ति को क्रोध छोड़ देना चाहिए ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0156","text":"प्रयत्न न करने पर कार्य में व्यवधान आ सकता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0157","text":"देव (भाग्य) को माननेवाले जीवन में सफल नहीं होते ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0158","text":"जो अपने कार्य के विषय में अपनी आवश्यकताओं का पालन-पोषण नहीं कर सकता ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0159","text":"जो अपने कार्य की उपेक्षा करता है वह अनेक दोष प्राप्त करता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0160","text":"प्रत्यक्ष, अनुमान आदि प्रमाणों से कार्य की परीक्षा करनी चाहिए ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0161","text":"जिस काम के लिए किसी व्यक्ति में प्रयत्न होना चाहिए, उसे ही नियुक्त करना चाहिए ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0162","text":"सोच-विचार करके कार्य करने से निर्मित व्यवस्था स्वीकार्य पाई जाती है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0163","text":"अपनी सामर्थ्य के अनुसार ही काम करना चाहिए ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0164","text":"अपनी सामर्थ्य से अधिक काम करनेवाला मूर्ख होता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0165","text":"कार्य करने के बाद संतुष्ट व्यक्ति सुख प्राप्त करता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0166","text":"अनुद्यमी, यानि आलसी व्यक्ति का कार्य सफल नहीं होता ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0167","text":"गांव के स्वभाव से परिचित व्यक्ति ही उसका सही देख रेख कर सकता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0168","text":"दुष्ट लोगों के संबंध अच्छे नहीं होते और वे अपने कार्यों को बिगाड़ देते हैं ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0169","text":"दुष्ट लोगों के संबंध अच्छे नहीं होते ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0170","text":"सरल स्वभाववाला राजा अपनी आश्रित प्रजा की रक्षा करता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0171","text":"राजा को प्रजा से बहुत प्रेम करना चाहिए ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0172","text":"राजा का दुख प्रजा का दुख है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0173","text":"दुर्बल राजा बलवान राजा के समान होता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0174","text":"जो सार्वभौमिक रूप से दूसरों का उद्बोधन करता है, वह प्रकाश की ओर बढ़ता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0175","text":"आलसी व्यक्ति दूसरों का नाश करता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0176","text":"सत्य, शील और ज्ञान व्यक्ति को महान बनाता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0177","text":"विश्वास व्यक्ति को सिद्धि देता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0178","text":"अविश्वास से कार्य नहीं सिद्ध होता ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0179","text":"अविश्वास व्यक्ति को सिद्धि नहीं देता ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0180","text":"संसार रहित व्यक्ति सिद्धि प्राप्त करता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0181","text":"दूसरे की संपत्ति को नहीं लेना चाहिए ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0182","text":"दान करना धर्म है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0183","text":"धन कमाने का सबसे अच्छा उपाय व्यापार है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0184","text":"संतोषी व्यक्ति सुख प्राप्त करता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0185","text":"संतोषी व्यक्ति का कार्य सिद्ध होता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0186","text":"झूठ बोलने से संतोष नहीं होता ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0187","text":"झूठ बोलने से दुःख होता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0188","text":"सदाचार का परिणाम सुख है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0189","text":"बिना धर्म के किया गया काम सुख नहीं देता ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0190","text":"गुरु को प्रणाम करना चाहिए ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0191","text":"गुरु की सेवा से ही विद्या प्राप्त होती है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0192","text":"गुरु को प्रसन्न करना चाहिए ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0193","text":"सत्य ही धर्म का मूल है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0194","text":"किसी का विश्वास भंग नहीं करना चाहिए ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0195","text":"किसी का विश्वास भंग करनेवाला अधर्म करता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0196","text":"मित्र से वैर दुःख देता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0197","text":"शत्रु के दुख से सुख मिलता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0198","text":"अपने दुर्बलता को छिपाकर रखना चाहिए ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0199","text":"अपने वास में आए हुए शत्रु का नाश करना चाहिए ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0200","text":"स्त्रियों की दुर्बलता से दुःख होता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0201","text":"सज्जनों द्वारा किया गया अपमान अथवा दुर्जनों द्वारा किया गया सत्कार दोनों से दुःख होता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0202","text":"अनेक कामों में सफलता प्राप्त करने वाला व्यक्ति धैर्यवान होता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0203","text":"राजा को आलस और क्रोध आदि महत्वपूर्ण कार्य में बाधक होते हैं ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0204","text":"लड़ाई-झगड़े की प्रवृत्ति मूर्खों का लक्षण है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0205","text":"मूर्खों के साथ विवाद नहीं करना चाहिए ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0206","text":"मूर्खों के साथ विवाद करना दुःख देता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0207","text":"मूर्खों से लोहा नहीं काटना चाहिए ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0208","text":"बुद्धिमान व्यक्ति मूर्खों से विवाद नहीं करता ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0209","text":"धर्म से ही संतोष होता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0210","text":"दया और दान का मूल धर्म है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0211","text":"दया से ही धर्म और अर्थ सिद्ध होता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0212","text":"व्यक्ति धर्म पालन से ही जीतता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0213","text":"मृत्यु भी धर्म पालन करनेवाले व्यक्ति का कुछ नहीं कर सकती ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0214","text":"धर्म से ही मृत्यु पर विजय मिलती है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0215","text":"धर्म-विरुद्ध पाप का प्रसार अधर्म का कारण है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0216","text":"अधर्म से ही विनाश होता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0217","text":"अधर्म विनाश का कारण है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0218","text":"दुष्टों के रहस्य (गुप्त बातों) को कभी नहीं सुनना चाहिए ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0219","text":"कठोर होना अधर्म है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0220","text":"कठोर व्यक्ति अधर्म करता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0221","text":"अपनों से शत्रुता दुःख देती है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0222","text":"झूठ बोलना अधर्म है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0223","text":"सत्य ही अधर्म का नाश करता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0224","text":"दूसरों पर विश्वास नहीं करना चाहिए ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0225","text":"दूसरों पर विश्वास करनेवाला व्यक्ति मूर्ख होता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0226","text":"बाह्य व्यवहार में सावधान रहना चाहिए ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0227","text":"अविश्वास हानिकारक होता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0228","text":"अज्ञात विषय में हस्तक्षेप नहीं करना चाहिए ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0229","text":"उपयुक्त समय पर किया गया काम सफलता देता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0230","text":"उच्च कुल में उत्पन्न व्यक्ति का सम्मान करना चाहिए ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0231","text":"नीच व्यक्ति का अपमान नहीं करना चाहिए ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0232","text":"आलसी व्यक्ति का कार्य सिद्ध नहीं होता ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0233","text":"व्यक्ति को उसकी अवस्था के अनुसार ही सम्मान देना चाहिए ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0234","text":"अपने स्थान पर स्थिर रहने पर ही आदर मिलता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0235","text":"मनुष्य का अहङ्कार कभी नहीं करना चाहिए ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0236","text":"मर्यादा का अतिक्रमण कभी नहीं करना चाहिए ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0237","text":"ऋण दुःख का मूल है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0238","text":"ऋण (निवारण तथा सुखप्राप्ति) स्वयं ही दूसरा नहीं है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0239","text":"स्त्री का मिलना कठिन होता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0240","text":"सभी प्रकार के कार्यों में धन्य का भाव श्रेष्ठ होता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0241","text":"आलसी व्यक्ति ज्ञान प्राप्त नहीं कर सकता ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0242","text":"काम में आसक्त पुरुष कार्य सिद्ध नहीं करता ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0243","text":"फूल-फल की इच्छा करनेवाला व्यक्ति सुख को कभी नहीं छोड़ता ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0244","text":"बिना धन के कोई काम करने की सोचना बालू में तेल निकालने के समान है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0245","text":"महत्वाकांक्षी को कभी उपहास नहीं करना चाहिए ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0246","text":"कार्य संपन्न करते समय, लक्ष्य पूर्ण होने पर सिद्धि मिलती है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0247","text":"लक्ष्य पूर्ण होने पर सिद्धि मिलती है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0248","text":"पति के अधीन रहनेवाली स्त्री ही कार्य में सफल होती है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0249","text":"गुरु के अधीन रहने वाला अर्थात आज्ञाकारी शिष्य ही कार्य में सफल होता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0250","text":"पिता का आज्ञाकारी ही पुत्र कहलाता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0251","text":"आज्ञाकारी व्यक्ति सफलता प्राप्त करता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0252","text":"स्वामी की आज्ञा का निष्फल भाव से पालन करनेवाला ही सच्चा सेवक है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0253","text":"माता पिता बालक को जितना देती है उतना दूसरा नहीं देता ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0254","text":"स्वामी से विरोध नहीं करना चाहिए ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0255","text":"स्वामी से विरोध करनेवाला दुःख प्राप्त करता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0256","text":"अधिक समय साथ-साथ रहने से मन-मुटाव होता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0257","text":"क्रोध न करनेवाला व्यक्ति संतोष प्राप्त करता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0258","text":"अपकारी व्यक्ति पर क्रोध करने से पहले अपने को शांत करना चाहिए ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0259","text":"ऐसे कोई कार्य नहीं होता, जिसमें परेशानी न हो ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0260","text":"उत्तम मनुष्य होने के कारण शुभ कार्य करने में संकोच नहीं करना चाहिए ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0261","text":"व्यवहार से ही व्यक्ति का मूल्यांकन होता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0262","text":"स्त्री कोमल होती है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0263","text":"स्त्री कुशल होती है, उसे उसके कार्य के योग्य होता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0264","text":"जो विश्वसनीय हो, उस पर विश्वास करना चाहिए ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0265","text":"प्रमादी पर विश्वास नहीं करना चाहिए ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0266","text":"आलसी पर विश्वास नहीं करना चाहिए ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0267","text":"दानशील व्यक्ति का सम्मान करना चाहिए ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0268","text":"वेदों का ज्ञान ब्राह्मणों का उत्तम आभूषण है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0269","text":"धर्म (कर्तव्य-पालन) सभी प्राणियों का उत्तम आभूषण है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0270","text":"उपदेशों से युक्त देश ही विद्या के लिए उपयुक्त स्थान है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0271","text":"राजा द्वारा दिया गया अपना निवास स्थान ही रहने योग्य होता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0272","text":"राजा का क्रोध शत्रु को भी नष्ट कर देता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0273","text":"गुरु व राजा के पास जाने समय कुछ न कुछ भेंट रखना चाहिए ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0274","text":"रहने वाले पर विश्वास नहीं करना चाहिए ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0275","text":"राजपरिवार में रहने वाले व्यक्तियों को कभी अपमान नहीं करना चाहिए ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0276","text":"राजपरिवार से संबंध रखना चाहिए ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0277","text":"राजा की आज्ञा और उपदेशों का पालन करना चाहिए ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0278","text":"पुत्र हित में सब कुछ करना चाहिए ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0279","text":"पुत्र से बढ़कर कोई मित्र नहीं होता ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0280","text":"स्त्रियों के साथ शत्रुता नहीं करनी चाहिए ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0281","text":"स्त्रियों के साथ मित्रता नहीं करनी चाहिए ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0282","text":"पुत्रियों के साथ शत्रुता नहीं करनी चाहिए ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0283","text":"पुत्रियों के साथ मित्रता नहीं करनी चाहिए ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0284","text":"दास का कार्य स्वामी की सेवा करना है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0285","text":"दान पुण्य का फल है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0286","text":"उपकार का बदला उपकार से चुकाना चाहिए ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0287","text":"दुष्टों की कमी अनिष्ट नहीं करती ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0288","text":"शत्रु के समान दुष्ट कोई नहीं ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0289","text":"नीच व्यक्ति के साथ संबंध नहीं करना चाहिए ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0290","text":"जल (नदी, नाद तथा सरोवर आदि) में कभी मूत्र-विसर्जन नहीं करना चाहिए ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0291","text":"जल में मल-मूत्र त्याग नहीं करना चाहिए ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0292","text":"मन का जैसा शरीर (हृष्ट-पुष्ट, सुंदर-कुरूप तथा छोटा-मोटा) होता है, वैसा ही ज्ञान अर्थात मस्तिष्क का विकास होता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0293","text":"बुद्धि के अनुरूप ही मनुष्य श्रेष्ठता प्राप्त करता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0294","text":"आग में आग नहीं डालनी चाहिए अर्थात् क्रोधी व्यक्ति को और अधिक क्रोध नहीं दिलाना चाहिए ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0295","text":"तपस्वी पूजनीय होते हैं ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0296","text":"अनशन से भूख लगती है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0297","text":"अनशन से प्यास लगती है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0298","text":"वेदज्ञान धर्म का मूल है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0299","text":"धर्म का आचरण सिद्धि देता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0300","text":"सत्य एवं मधुर वाणी स्वर्ग की सीढ़ी है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0301","text":"सत्य से बढ़कर कोई तप नहीं ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0302","text":"सत्य ही स्वर्ग-प्राप्ति का आधार है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0303","text":"सत्य बोलने से ही देवता प्रसन्न होते हैं ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0304","text":"असत्य भाषण से कोई दुःख प्राप्त नहीं ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0305","text":"अपने गुरु के आगे झूठ नहीं बोलना चाहिए ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0306","text":"दुष्ट व्यक्ति का कोई मित्र नहीं होता ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0307","text":"दुष्ट व्यक्ति जीवन-निर्वाह मुश्किल होता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0308","text":"दानवीर सबसे बड़ा वीर है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0309","text":"गुरु, देवता और ब्राह्मणों में सेवा अर्थात् श्रद्धा-सम्मान का भाव रखना मानवता का आभूषण है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0310","text":"निंदक (निंदा करनेवाला) पाप का आभूषण है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0311","text":"कुलहीन व्यक्ति की अपेक्षा अकुलीन व्यक्ति श्रेष्ठ है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0312","text":"मंदाचार से आयु व यश में वृद्धि होती है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0313","text":"प्रिय बोलनेवाला, परंतु अनिष्ट कहनेवाला कभी नहीं बोलना चाहिए ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0314","text":"अनेक कार्यों को सिद्ध करनेवाला व्यक्ति ही एक व्यक्ति का अनुमान कर सकता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0315","text":"दुर्जनों के साथ अपना भाग्य नष्ट नहीं करना चाहिए ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0316","text":"जीवन में सफलता प्राप्त करनेवाले पुरुष अच्छे मित्र के साथ संबंध नहीं जोड़ना चाहिए ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0317","text":"ज्ञान, शत्रु व रोग को जड़ से उखाड़ फेंकना चाहिए ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0318","text":"अपने लिए कष्टकारी मार्ग पर चलना ही मनुष्य के लिए उत्तम है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0319","text":"याचकों से कभी घृणा नहीं करनी चाहिए ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0320","text":"मंदाचार से कार्य सिद्ध नहीं होता ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0321","text":"प्रमादी व्यक्ति कार्य सिद्ध नहीं करता ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0322","text":"राजा गुरु से दूर नहीं रहना चाहिए ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0323","text":"वेद, यजुर्वेद व सामवेद का ज्ञान पाप का नाश करता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0324","text":"स्वर्ग-प्राप्ति से बढ़कर कोई दुःख नहीं ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0325","text":"व्यक्ति शरीर त्यागने के बाद दुःख प्राप्त करता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0326","text":"रोगी मनुष्य की चिकित्सा सुख देती है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0327","text":"दुष्ट कुल का कलंक होता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0328","text":"दुष्ट पुत्र दुःख देता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0329","text":"दुष्ट स्त्री दुःख देती है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0330","text":"दुष्ट मित्र दुःख देता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0331","text":"दुष्ट सेवक दुःख देता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0332","text":"दुष्ट संबंधी दुःख देते हैं ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0333","text":"पति की आज्ञा का पालन करनेवाली स्त्री इस लोक में सुख और परलोक में सद्गति प्राप्त करती है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0334","text":"अतिथियों की सेवा सिद्धि देती है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0335","text":"न्याय से धर्म होता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0336","text":"पापी अपने पापों का फल भोगता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0337","text":"मनुष्य का व्यवहार उसके गुण को प्रकट करता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0338","text":"देवों का कार्य मनुष्यों द्वारा किया जाता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0339","text":"चोरों व सरकारी अधिकारियों से अपनी रक्षा करनी चाहिए ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0340","text":"अपनी प्रजा के दुःख को सुननेवाला राजा उनकी रक्षा करता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0341","text":"न्यायशील राजा इस लोक में सुख और परलोक में सद्गति प्राप्त करता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0342","text":"अहिंसा धर्म की कसौटी है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0343","text":"सज्जन अपने शरीर को दूसरों के लिए अर्पित करता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0344","text":"सभी प्राणियों को संतोष प्राप्त होता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0345","text":"ज्ञानी पुरुष का संतोष कभी नष्ट नहीं होता ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0346","text":"ज्ञान के दीपक से सांसारिक भय नष्ट हो जाता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0347","text":"शरीर व पुष्पों का आधार जड़ है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0348","text":"जन्म और मरण दुःख देता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."},{"id":"chanakya-hi-0349","text":"बुद्धिमान पुरुष जन्म-मरण के बंधन से मुक्ति के लिए प्रयत्न करता है ।","author":"Chanakya Niti — Hindi","source":"Hindi Wikiquote — Chanakya","tags":["language:hi","script:devanagari","tradition:chanakya","tradition:hindi","theme:wisdom","theme:statecraft"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":true,"verificationNote":"Verified via Hindi Wikiquote / curated public-domain source."}]}